Sentencas: Recent developments in solid oxide cells focus on decreasing operating temperatures below 600 degrees C for improved cost and electrochemical stability in order to improve viability for commercialization.
Titulo: Mechanisms of PrOx performance enhancement of oxygen electrodes for low and intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this work, we improve the performance and stability of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) and a recently developed electrode material, SrTi0.3Fe0.55Co0.15O3-delta (STFC), with addition of PrOx nanoparticles.
Titulo: Mechanisms of PrOx performance enhancement of oxygen electrodes for low and intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Single-step PrOx infiltration improves performance of both LSCF and STFC across all tested temperatures (450-650 degrees C) with the most significant enhancements at lower temperatures.
Titulo: Mechanisms of PrOx performance enhancement of oxygen electrodes for low and intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: STFC modified with PrOx yields the best overall performance and stability, with the initial polarization resistance of 0.20 Omega cm(2) at 550 degrees C increasing over similar to 800 h before stabilizing at 0.27 Omega cm(2).
Titulo: Mechanisms of PrOx performance enhancement of oxygen electrodes for low and intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This represents a factor of similar to 10 resistance decrease compared to the LSCF electrode at 550 degrees C. A distribution of relaxation times analysis sheds light on the electrochemical mechanisms impacted by PrOx.
Titulo: Mechanisms of PrOx performance enhancement of oxygen electrodes for low and intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
